# Mock Page Data Rules

## Page JSON Structure

Every page JSON must have this shape:

```json
{
  "slug": "/about",
  "locale": "en",
  "template": "default",
  "seo": {
    "title": "Page Title",
    "description": "Meta description",
    "ogImage": "https://..."
  },
  "blocks": [
    {
      "id": "unique-block-id",
      "type": "block-type-name",
      "props": { }
    }
  ]
}
```

## Block IDs

Every block `id` must be unique within the page. Use format `{type}-{number}` (e.g. `hero-1`, `room-list-1`).

## Dynamic Route Pages

For pages that match dynamic slugs (e.g. `/rooms/:roomId`), add a `slugPattern` field:

```json
{
  "slugPattern": "/rooms/:roomId",
  "slug": "/rooms/:roomId",
  "blocks": [...]
}
```

The mock adapter uses pattern matching to resolve these. Pattern pages are registered in `mock.adapter.ts` `patternFiles` array.

## File Naming

- Static pages: `{slug}.json` (e.g. `about.json`, `contact.json`)
- Home page: `home.json` (slug `/`)
- Nested slugs use `--` separator: `/rooms/all` → `rooms--all.json`
- Pattern pages: descriptive name (e.g. `room-detail.json`)

## Block `type` Must Match Registry

The `type` field must exactly match a key registered in `blocks/index.ts` via `registerTenantBlocks()`.
